laboratory_examinations.findings: The liver is diffusely echogenic with a smooth contour. No focal liver mass, the main portal vein is patent with hepatopetal flow, and no ascites noted. There is no intrahepatic biliary dilation. The gallbladder contains a few gallstones with marked wall thickening and wall edema but is not abnormally distended. Pancreas appears within normal limits, spleen is normal with a length of 9.9 cm, and kidneys have simple cysts up to 4.4 cm. Right kidney measures 11.7 cm and left kidney measures 11.6 cm.
No polymorphonuclear leukocytes seen. No microorganisms seen.
